Interface UserEvent

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AuthenticationSuccessEvent, TunnelCloseEvent, TunnelConnectEvent

    public interface UserEvent
    Abstract basis for events which may have an associated UserContext when triggered.

    Michael Jumper

      UserContext getUserContext()

      • getUserContext

        UserContext getUserContext()
        Returns the current UserContext of the user triggering the event, if any.
        Returns:
        The current UserContext of the user triggering the event, if any, or null if no UserContext is associated with the event.
